   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PUB.ACTION.LIST_CI_RELATIONS

= General description =
This action lists CI relations to an existing Configuration Item(CI) in CMDB in ServiceNow.

= Reference link =
https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/orlando-application-development/page/integrate/inbound-rest/concept/cmdb-instance-api.html#cmdb-instance-GET-classname-sysid

= Inputs =
* Class Name* : Provide CMDB class name to list its relations. E.g. cmdb_ci_linux_server.
* System ID*  : Provide system id of the configuration item to list its relations. E.g. 7c477dc60f943b402cc2cd8ce1050e45.
* CI Fields   : Specify comma-separated name of configuration item fields to return in the response. E.g. sys_id, name.
* Limit       : Provide maximum number of relations returned.

= Failure Conditions =
* If an invalid class name or system id is provided.
* If invalid connection details are provided.

= Behavior =
NOTE:  If Limit is 0, current API lists all inbound and outbound relations for a CI.

= Return Value =
UC4RB_SN_INBOUND_REL#  : Inbound Relations
UC4RB_SN_OUTBOUND_REL# : Outbound Relations

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)

= Logging =
logs will be displayed in the AE report.

= Example =
Class Name : cmdb_ci_linux_server
System ID  : 7c477dc60f943b402cc2cd8ce1050e45
CI Fields  : sys_id, name.
Limit      : 100



]]></Docu>
      </row>
   </documentation>
